
                                            The Defence Ministry's Mafi Mgobozi says the soldier tried to kill himself after shooting the woman.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The South African Defence Force (SANDF) has confirmed that a female officer deployed to the Democratic Republic of Congo has been shot and killed, allegedly by another South African soldier. The Defence Ministry's Mafi Mgobozi says the soldier then tried to kill himself after shooting the woman, who's believed to be his girlfriend. The man is currently in a critical condition at a hospital in Goma. Mgobozi says the motive behind the shooting is currently being probed. “He shot her and then tried to commit suicide. He is currently in hospital. We are still investigating the reason.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)